@node "intro" "Introduction"
@next "legal"
@prev "main"

I was really getting sick of using an old copy of PC-Task and Xlink85 to
move files between my Ti-85 and my Amiga so I decided to try and write
my own software.  Thankfully there was a half decent Linux program
called Xlink85(See @{"Acknowledgements" link "ack"}) at www.ticalc.org 
that was a great base for it.  Because of that I only had to deal with
the actually serial port manipulation.

@endnode

