@node "ack" "THANK YOU VERY MUCH!!!"
@prev "author"

Except for the low level IO routines in tiport.c this program is based on
the Linux/DOS program XLink by Jani Halme (jaadha@utu.fi).

send() and recv() are based on the examples in linkprot.txt by Per
Finander(pfimdt93@tufvan.hv.se)

The file ti-prot.txt by Pascal Bouron(bouron@ENS-Cachan.fr) was also 
very useful.

Also very helpful was the formats.zip file by David Brodbeck
(gull@cyberspace.com) which explained the layout of the #?.85? files.

www.ticalc.org is the nets best source for TI calculator programs and info.

This program was created on an Amiga 3000 by Commodore.  Too bad they
screwed up and went under.  Let's hope that GW2k can take us somewhere
good.

Thanks to the GNU project for making the tools used to create this
program and to Fred Fish and the ADE project for porting them to the
Amiga.

@endnode
